
# main-overview

## Development Guidelines

- Only modify code directly relevant to the specific request. Avoid changing unrelated functionality.
- Never replace code with placeholders like `# ... rest of the processing ...`. Always include complete code.
- Break problems into smaller steps. Think through each step separately before implementing.
- Always provide a complete PLAN with REASONING based on evidence from code and logs before making changes.
- Explain your OBSERVATIONS clearly, then provide REASONING to identify the exact issue. Add console logs when needed to gather more information.


This project consists entirely of auto-generated API client code and interfaces without implemented business logic. The codebase contains:

- Generated TypeScript API clients
- Interface definitions and DTOs
- Request/response type structures
- HTTP client configuration

Business Logic Assessment:
The codebase does not contain executable business rules or domain-specific implementations. All files are technical interface layers that define API contracts but delegate actual business processing to server-side components not included in these sources.

Component Structure:
1. API Client Layer
- API endpoint definitions
- Request/response DTOs
- Authentication handling

2. Type Definitions
- Data transfer objects
- API response wrappers
- Enum declarations

Importance Score: 0/100
Justification: Contains no business logic implementations, only generated interface code and API client wrappers.

